Assisted by Jacob Caithamer; used my underwater camera w built in thermometer as thermometer provided by DNR does not work.  Mostly sunny- 75 F- wind southwest 3 mph.  1 adult loon and 1 young loon.
Adult loon and young loon observed.

column1: Sunny- south wind at 8 mph- 75 F.
Lots of boaters on the water as it is a Saturday and Memorial Day weekend.
Numerous black terns feeding over the lake.

2 loons- weather is 70 degrees- north wind 1 mph- mostly sunny.
weather is 75 F- mostly cloudy- wind nw 8 mph; saw 1 common loon and 2 gulls (I think ring bills)
Mostly cloudy- 73 F- wind E 6 mph; saw 2 adult common loons
sunny- south breeze at 5 mph- 73 F
mostly cloudy- wind 7 mph from north- saw 1 common loon
1 common loon- mostly sunny- wind northwest at 7 mph- 83 degrees
mostly cloudy- 81 F- wind ssw 7 mph; 3 common loons; assistance by Benjamin F. Caithamer and Jacob G. Caithamer

Mostly clear- 80 F- wind west 7 mph- 1 common loon
Mostly sunny- 82 degrees F- wind west 3 mph but variable.  1 double-crested cormorant- 10 gulls (possibly ring-billed gulls).
Partly cloudy- wind nw 5-10 mph- one common loon.
Partly sunny turning to cloudy- wind south 5 mph- air temp 80 F.  Two adult loons but no young loons.  Several black terns flying about.
Weather: mostly clear- wind SSE 10 mph- 83 degrees F; finished collecting data at 3:10 pm.  Saw 1 common loon.
Weather was 70 degrees F- wind WNW 5-15 mph- mostly clear.  I saw an adult black tern while sampling; yesterday evening I saw 4 young of year black terns.
Weather is cloudy- south wind 3 mph- 82 F.  Saw one adult bald eagle on my way out to sample.

mostly cloudy- 70 degrees F- wind SE 5 mph- saw 1 common loon- 2 black terns- and 1 great blue heron.  In the north bay- where I live- there have been mats of dead filamentous algae.  The algae bloom peaked around May 28.  This is the first time in 21 years that I remember having an algae bloom this early and this extensive.
Mostly sunny- 80 degrees F- wind NNW 8 mph; finished at 2:45 pm
Mostly cloudy- 75 degrees F- wind SSE 15 mph; saw 1 adult common loon and 2 young of the year common loons; also saw 1 gull that was probably a ring billed gull.
mostly sunny- then brief shower; 73 F- wind North 5-10 mph- 1 adult common loon
Weather = clear- 80F- NW wind 3-5 mph.  Saw 3 adult and 2 young common loons.

It is a warm and sunny Sunday afternoon.  Boat traffic is moderate but personal watercraft (jet ski) traffic is constant.  I had one pwc doing circles and creating massive waves within 200 feet of my boat.  Its waves rocked my boat so much that it knocked my sampling reagents and glassware off the top of my cooler and onto the floor of my boat.  And at another time I had a motor boat come within about 40 feet of me creating a significant wake.  I spoke in a normal voice to the operator: "You are too close-" which he ignored.

column1: Weather is 77 F- wind NW 3 mph- mostly sunny.  I saw no loons today- nor any other wildlife.
